items.title: Recap: FLA 2, BUF 3 - F/SO
items.blurb: Ullmark, Sabres top Panthers in SO
items.description: Linus Ullmark recorded 41 saves to help propel the Sabres over the Panthers in a shootout, on home ice, 3-2

items.title: Dadonov trims the deficit
items.blurb: FLA@BUF: Dadonov beats Ullmark on the rush
items.description: Evgenii Dadonov moves in on the rush and beats Linus Ullmark's right pad to the near post, trimming the Panthers' deficit to 2-1 in the 3rd

items.title: Larsson opens the scoring
items.blurb: FLA@BUF: Larsson lifts wrist shot past Bobrovsky
items.description: Johan Larsson roofs a wrist shot off the feed from Kyle Okposo on the rush to give the Sabres a 1-0 lead in the 2nd

items.title: Ullmark's glove save
items.blurb: FLA@BUF: Ullmark uses glove to deny Hoffman
items.description: Mike Hoffman rips a wrist shot from the slot, but Linus Ullmark uses his glove to make the save in the 1st period

items.title: Bobrovsky stones Mittelstadt
items.blurb: FLA@BUF: Bobrovsky denies Mittelstadt on the break
items.description: Casey Mittelstadt moves in on the break and lets go of a wrister, but Sergei Bobrovsky turns it away in the 1st

items.title: Mittelstadt's shootout goal
items.blurb: FLA@BUF: Mittelstadt wins game for Sabres in shootout
items.description: Casey Mittelstadt skates in and goes to his backhand to beat Sergei Bobrovsky and win the shootout for the Sabres

items.title: Scandella doubles the lead
items.blurb: FLA@BUF: Scandella finishes off the feed from Okposo
items.description: Kyle Okposo sends a dish to Marco Scandella who fires a wrist shot into the back of the net, doubling the Sabres' lead to 2-0 in the 3rd

items.title: Hoffman's clutch goal
items.blurb: FLA@BUF: Hoffman nets wrist shot for late equalizer
items.description: Mike Hoffman rips a wrist shot past Linus Ullmark's glove side to tie the game at 2 late in the 3rd period

result.description: Jakob Silfverberg (2) Wrist Shot, assists: Rickard Rakell (1), Hampus Lindholm (4)
Cam Fowler (2) Wrist Shot, assists: Ondrej Kase (3), Jacob Larsson (1)
Pierre-Luc Dubois (1) Wrist Shot, assists: Seth Jones (2)

items.title: ANA @ CBJ
items.blurb: Condensed Game: Ducks @ Blue Jackets
items.description: Extended highlights of the Anaheim Ducks at the Columbus Blue Jackets

items.title: Recap: ANA 2, CBJ 1
items.blurb: Silfverberg, Fowler find twine to power Ducks' win
items.description: Jakob Silfverberg netted a shorthanded goal in the 2nd and Cam Fowler doubled the lead less than two minutes later en route to a 2-1 victory

items.title: Fowler's wrister beats Korpisalo
items.blurb: ANA@CBJ: Fowler rifles Kase's feed into the twine
items.description: Ondrej Kase drops a pass to Cam Fowler on the rush and he wires a wrister past Joonas Korpisalo to quickly double the Ducks' lead to 2-0

items.title: Silfverberg nets shorthanded goal
items.blurb: ANA@CBJ: Silfverberg finds rebound, scores SHG
items.description: Jakob Silfverberg jams home a rebound near the net while on the shorthanded rush to put the Ducks on the board first in the 2nd period

items.title: Miller shuts down Nyquist
items.blurb: ANA@CBJ: Miller sticks out his pad to stuff Nyquist
items.description: Ryan Miller quickly shuffles across the crease and seals the post to deny Gustav Nyquist's wraparound attempt and preserve a scoreless 1st

items.title: Korpisalo's superb glove save
items.blurb: ANA@CBJ: Korpisalo robs Kase at the doorstep
items.description: Joonas Korpisalo makes an initial save, then snares Ondrej Kase's point-blank chance from his backside for a brilliant stop in the 2nd period

items.title: Miller's outstanding stick save
items.blurb: ANA@CBJ: Miller denies Jones' shorthanded bid
items.description: Ryan Miller pokes the puck away from Seth Jones on a shorthanded odd-man rush to deny a golden opportunity and retain a 2-1 lead for the Ducks

items.title: Dubois scores from sharp angle
items.blurb: ANA@CBJ: Dubois nets sharp angle wrister off Miller
items.description: Pierre-Luc Dubois powers into the zone and slings a wrister from a tough angle that sneaks past Ryan Miller to cut the deficit in half

Andrei Svechnikov (1) Snap Shot, assists: Jordan Staal (3)

items.title: Recap: NYI 2, CAR 5
items.blurb: Canes top Isles to notch best start in team history
items.description: Teuvo Teravainen and Brett Pesce scored a goal to fuel the Hurricanes' 5-2 win, as they improve to 5-0-0 for the first time in team history

items.title: Boychuk's scorching PPG
items.blurb: NYI@CAR: Boychuk blisters a slap shot past Mrazek
items.description: Johnny Boychuk winds up and blasts the puck off the boards past Petr Mrazek, tying the game at 2 with a power-play goal

items.title: Teravainen buries Hamilton's dish
items.blurb: NYI@CAR: Hamilton, Teravainen connect on the rush
items.description: Dougie Hamilton carries into the zone on a 2-on-1 rush then makes a great pass to Teuvo Teravainen, who puts into the open net

items.title: Nelson's power-play goal
items.blurb: NYI@CAR: Nelson taps Bailey's dish home on power play
items.description: Josh Bailey takes Jordan Eberle's pass and feeds Brock Nelson down low, where he puts it into the net for a power-play goal

items.title: Haula's second-chance goal
items.blurb: NYI@CAR: Haula puts home his own rebound in tight
items.description: Erik Haula's initial shot is turned away by Thomas Greiss, but he grabs his own rebound and tucks it home to give the Hurricanes a 3-2 lead

items.title: Svechnikov's empty-net tally
items.blurb: NYI@CAR: Svechnikov pots empty-netter to seal win
items.description: Andrei Svechnikov takes the puck the length of the ice after the face-off win and puts it into the empty net to open up a 5-2 Hurricanes' lead

items.title: Pesce snipes home a goal
items.blurb: NYI@CAR: Pesce wires a wrister by Greiss in tight
items.description: Brett Pesce takes Andrei Svechnikov's pass inside the circle and rips it past Thomas Greiss to give the Hurricanes a 2-1 lead in the 1st

items.title: Hamilton's one-time snipe
items.blurb: NYI@CAR: Hamilton slings Niederreiter's pass home
items.description: Dougie Hamilton winds up and hammers Nino Niederreiter's drop pass into the net, doubling the Hurricanes' lead late in the 2nd period
